        "title": "docs: document portable coordinator and BYOI operations",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add comprehensive runbooks for the portable Node/PostgreSQL coordinator and bring-your-own-infrastructure integrations\n- document registered lease ownership, routing, heartbeat, sharing, bridge, rollback, deployment, restore, and security boundaries\n- force native VNC and WebVNC SSH forwards onto IPv4 loopback even when user SSH configuration enables gateway ports\n- update documentation indexes, source map, examples, and changelog\n\n## Verification\n\n- `scripts/check-docs.sh`\n- `go test ./internal/cli -count=1`\n- `go test -race ./internal/cli -run 'TestVNCTunnelCommand|TestGuardMacOSDirectWebVNC|TestOpenURLCommand' -count=1`\n- autoreview: clean\n- public added-line confidentiality scan: zero internal terms\n\n## Security\n\nThe VNC tunnel now passes `GatewayPorts=no` and binds its local forward and generated endpoint explicitly to `127.0.0.1`. Manual VNC examples use the same boundary.\n",
